data.description_objectives:
The survey aims to delineate the subsurface architecture of the Kalkaroo Fault Zone and associated structural corridors to better understand their role as potential hydrothermal fluid pathways. Specific objectives include: 
(1) mapping resistivity contrasts across the orebody and domes to identify conductive horizons in the host stratigraphy; 
(2) imaging the geometry and depth extent of the Kalkaroo Fault Zone to assess its connectivity to deeper crustal or mantle structures; 
(3) integrating MT-derived resistivity models with magnetic, gravity, and drilling data to refine geological interpretations; and 
(4) evaluating the mineral systems context by linking local-scale structures to regional-scale tectonic features in the Curnamona Province. The outcomes will guide further exploration, support 3D geological model development, and contribute to understanding the fluid-rock interactions that control mineralisation in this part of South Australia.
